<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HR01944</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : A RESOLUTION DIRECTING THE APPROPRIATE HOUSE COMMITTEE TO CONDUCT AN INQUIRY, IN AID OF LEGISLATION, ON THE STATUS OF THE RECONSTRUCTION PLANS, RELIEF, AND REHABILITATION EFFORTS FOR MARAWI CITY, INCLUDING A REVIEW OF THE UTILIZATION OF ALL DISBURSED FUNDS FOR SUCH EFFORTS AND THE EXAMINATION OF THE PRESCRIBED GUIDELINES USED IN THE SELECTION OF PRIVATE CONTRACTORS THAT WILL LEAD THE REHABILITATION EFFORTS IN MARAWI CITY, WITH THE END IN VIEW OF ENSURING THAT THE GOVERNMENT, THROUGH THE TASK FORCE BANGON MARAWI, WILL BE ABLE TO DELIVER ON ITS COMMITMENT TO PRIORITIZE  THE POST-DISASTER RECOVERY OF MARAWI CITY THROUGH EFFICIENT, EFFECTIVE, AND TRANSPARENT MEANS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON RULES ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>